### Document Analysis Summary

**PRD Analysis (docs/PRD.md - 53KB, 1176 lines):**

*Core Requirements Identified:*
- **8 Functional Requirement Sections:** FR-1 (User Account Management) through FR-8 (Subscription & Tier Management)
- **Success Criteria:** User-focused outcomes (100+ users, 20% premium conversion, 50%+ 30-day retention)
- **Business Model:** Freemium with specific limits (1 pet, 50 health records, 100 expenses/month, 10 reminders, 100MB storage)
- **Timeline:** 14-day MVP development target
- **Technology Stack:** React 18, Vite, Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage), Stripe, OneSignal, Resend, Vercel
- **Non-Functional Requirements:** Performance (<2s page load), Security (GDPR, RLS), Scalability (10K+ users, <$0.10/user/month)

*Scope Boundaries:*
- MVP: 7 core features (auth, pets, health, expenses, reminders, documents, subscription)
- Explicitly excluded from MVP: Multi-user accounts, receipt OCR, medication tracking, vet portal integration, native mobile apps
- Post-MVP Phase 2/Vision features clearly documented

*Key Architectural Constraints from PRD:*
- Mobile-first responsive design (640px primary target)
- Single Page Application (SPA) architecture - no SSR needed
- Row Level Security (RLS) mandatory for data isolation
- Free tier limits enforced backend-first (not just UI)
- Dual notification system (OneSignal push + Resend email for redundancy)

**Architecture Document Analysis (docs/architecture.md - 62KB, 2070 lines):**

*Technology Decisions (All Versions Verified Nov 2025):*
- React 19.2.0, TypeScript 5.9.3, Vite (latest), Tailwind CSS 4.0, React Router 7.9.4
- Supabase (PostgreSQL 15/17), Stripe API 2025-10-29.clover, Playwright 1.56.1, Vitest 4.0
- Complete stack: 25+ technology decisions with rationale for each

*Implementation Patterns Defined:*
- 10 mandatory patterns for AI agent consistency
- Naming conventions (files, database, components, functions)
- Component structure pattern (exact order: imports ‚Üí types ‚Üí hooks ‚Üí handlers ‚Üí JSX)
- Database schema pattern (RLS policies, CASCADE DELETE, indexes)
- Supabase query pattern (always check error first)
- Form validation pattern (React Hook Form + Zod)
- State management pattern (React Context)
- Error handling pattern (consistent messages)
- Styling pattern (Tailwind class order, mobile-first)
- Date/time handling (UTC storage, local display)

*Database Schema:*
- 7 tables defined: profiles, pets, health_records, expenses, budgets, reminders, documents
- All tables have RLS policies with SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE rules
- Foreign keys with CASCADE DELETE
- Indexes on frequently queried columns

*Epic to Architecture Mapping:*
- Clear mapping of all 7 epics to architectural components

**Epics Document Analysis (docs/epics.md - 78KB, 1873 lines):**

